did.abstract: This collection contains records from the period in which Robert Morris served as Dean of the University College (1966-1970) and Dean of Undergraduate Studies (1970- roughly 1977).
did.physloc: The materials are located onsite in the department.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Files containing student grades and personally identifying information removed in 2018 by Miles Lawlor. Meeting minutes for the Committee on Academic Standing removed because they contained student grades and personally identifying information. Files regarding student litigation against the univerity removed as they contained student grades.

bioghist.head: Biographical Sketch
bioghist.p: Robert Morris started at the State University of New York at Albany in 1966 as Dean of the University College, which had been established in 1963 to oversee academic affairs for freshmen and sophomores. The University College presided over nearly every aspect of academic life for underclassmen, including academic probation, advisement, attendance, and withdrawal. He was later promoted to Dean of Undergraduate Studies, a position in which he oversaw both lower- and upper-division undergraduate education, from 1970 until approximately 1977. Between these two positions, he oversaw all aspects of the administration of undergraduate education at the University, with a focus on the drafting, creation and implementation of policies for students in the lower division.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection addresses all aspects of the administration of undergraduate education at the University. It includes undergraduate policy manuals, advisement manuals for professors, documentation on changes in various grading policies, correspondence between Morris and various other administrators at the University, budget materials, annual reports, enrollment data, and planning documentation for the Undergraduate Bulletin. There is also correspondence between employees of the University College and other colleges and universities relating to policy creation. The bulk of the material is dated between 1966 and 1978.

arrangement.head: Arrangement of the Collection
arrangement.p: Files in this collection have been maintained in their original order upon processing.
